I get so emotional sometimes&hellip;
I had arrived at the hospital to visit a friend. I hadn&rsquo;t seen her for 14 years before the previous time which was some months ago. And now I wanted to visit - as at our age you never know.
There were freshly planted trees dotted across the plaza. They were mere saplings - young upstarts - and the delicate pale leaves fluttered slightly in a breeze that wasn&rsquo;t there.
